{"word":"G1689 - ἐμβλέπω - emblépō - em-blep'-o - Behold","slug":"G1689","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἐμβλέπω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>emblépō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>em-blep'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Behold"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B5;&#x0313;&#x03BC;&#x03B2;&#x03BB;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C0;&#x03C9; - emblepo&#x0304;</b> - <i>em-blep'-o</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G1722\">G1722</a> and <a href=\"#/G991\">G991</a>; to <i>look on</i>, that is, (relatively) to <i>observe</i> fixedly, or (absolutely) to <i>discern</i> clearly: - behold, gaze up, look upon, (could) see."}]}